@node config "EASys!, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: System environment..."
@prev main

   @{" < " link main} @{b}EASys! Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________


   @{b}Please configure your System for EASys!-usage@{ub}

   The configurations which are discussed herein, are available
   within the multi-function commodity "MCP". Similar functions
   should be also available to "MultiCX" as well as by using
   separate system-utilities from aminet. Those functions used
   here, are known to be programmed system-conformly and do
   have any negative constraints to your system stability.

   Please, activate those functions:

   * "Default PubScreen". Hereby, the frontmost screen will
     automatically become the preset public screen for the
     system.

   * "PubModi" including "Shanghai". Hereby, new public windows
     (such as those of EASys!) will always be opened
     automatically on the actually preset public screen.

   * "Screen Activation". The frontmost screen is being activated
     right after it has been brought to front. No additional
     mouse-click into the screen or a screen's window is needed
     to start working on the screen.

   * SUN-Options: Sun-Mouse, delay "2". Hereby, the window
     under the mouse-pointer will only be activated, when you
     move the mousepointer over the window and stop moving for
     a short while. Windows popping up immediately (such as
     requesters) will stay activated as long as you don't
     move the mousepointer at that moment.


   further on (NewEdit, RTPatch) and:

   * Just let install the example configuration for EASys! &
     ToolManager. The newest ToolManager Release 3.1 is included
     with the packet and may be installed fully functional withing
     the installation procedure. Note, that for later configuring
     ToolManager, you will need at least the MUI 3.0 Demo version
     readily installed to your system (not needed for pure Tool-
     Manager functionality!).

