@node apps "EASys!, ©'1998 by Thomas Neidhardt: Applications..."
@prev main

   @{" < " link main} @{b}EASys! Wizards@{ub}

        ©'98 Thomas Neidhardt, 91058 Erlangen, GERMANY
____________________________________________________________________


   @{b}EASys! functional enhancements for external programs ...@{ub}

   just enhance all programs that offer menus or buttons for
   reservation of Shell-Commandlines. Important is, that they
   do as well offer parameter-handling for actually used
   files...


   ... especially for use in the following tools/apps:


   @{b}ToolManager@{ub}-Dock / Menu
   just use the delivered example-config:

   (rshift F4) the EASys! PresentationManager
   (rShift F5) ... FileManager
   (rShift F6) ... FileStarter

   @{b}ScreenTab@{ub} (s. Aminet, by Michael Link)
   according to my usability-tests, this is the most
   versatile, stable, and best ported Start/Task-Bar for
   the AMIGA.

   Use this for comfortably calling the EASys! Search-/
   Replace functions and the EASys!-Preferences as well
   as all your Office- and Program-References which have
   been installed by EASys!.

   If you are a registered ScreenTab user, you may later
   also enhance the Dirwalker-Plugins by EASys!-Plugins
   (see ExampleConfigs)

   @{b}YAM@{ub}:
   Build-in the Filetype-analyzing-Utility "IDer" which
   has been delivered ready-to-start preconfigured with
   EASys!, by entering the following Shell-Command-Entry
   for all Mime-Types:

   ${RefTable/View-Master} %s

   @{b}IBrowse@{ub}:
   Build-in the "IDer" (s. YAM) by supplying the following
   Shell-Command-Entry:

   ${RefTable/View-Master} %s

   for every external viewn formats such as
   MPEG-Video, MPEG-Audio, AVI, txt, readme...

   Configure IBrowse also to use the following commandline
   for automatically calling the EMail-Program YAM:

   Use Preferences/Network/EMail "external"
   for "MailTo" and "SendMail":

   run >NIL: sys:rexxc/rx EASys!_rexx:Start_Mail_Addr.rexx %h


   @{b}SimpleFind@{ub}:
   SimpleFind is included with EASys!. It has been
   installed to EASys!_bin: and is readily preconfigured
   for EASys! functionality.

   @{b}Picture-Manager@{ub}:
   Example-Scripts are included within the Packet
   (see directory EASys!:Extras).

   @{b}GoldEd@{ub}:
   Build-in the File-Management functions of the EASys!
   FileManager (sorry, but this task will need an
   experienced GoldEd User ... or a workshop).

   (... just have also a look to @{" + " SYSTEM "EASys!_bin:fm -DIR easys!:exampleconfigs"} EASys!:ExampleConfigs/ )


____________________________________________________________________
@endnode

